{
  "info": {
    "name": "Task Management API - Demo Sessions",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for Week 22 Demo Sessions - Task Management API\n\nThis collection demonstrates all concepts taught in the demo:\n- User Registration & Authentication\n- JWT Token Management\n- Profile Management\n- CRUD Operations for Tasks\n- Query Filters\n- Error Handling\n\n**Usage:**\n1. Create environment: Local or Production\n2. Set base_url variable\n3. Run register ‚Üí login ‚Üí save token automatically\n4. All protected routes will use saved token",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user data\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('email');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('name');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.not.have.property('password');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["users", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Register a new user account.\n\n**Validations:**\n- Email must be valid format\n- Password minimum 8 characters\n- Name 2-50 characters\n\n**Demo Concepts:**\n- DTOs with class-validator\n- Password hashing with bcrypt\n- Custom pipes (TrimPipe, LowercasePipe)\n- Duplicate email check"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200 or 201\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has access token\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('user');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save access token to environment",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"access_token\", jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    console.log(\"‚úÖ Access token saved to environment\");",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login with email and password to get JWT token.\n\n**Returns:**\n- access_token: JWT token valid for 24 hours\n- user: User information\n\n**Demo Concepts:**\n- Password verification with bcrypt\n- JWT token generation\n- Token payload structure\n- Auto-save token to environment"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login - Invalid Credentials",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 401\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Error message is correct\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.message).to.eql('Invalid credentials');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"wrongpassword\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Test error handling for wrong password.\n\n**Expected:**\n- Status: 401 Unauthorized\n- Message: \"Invalid credentials\"\n\n**Security Note:**\n- Same error message for wrong password or non-existent user\n- Prevents email enumeration attacks"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Authentication endpoints demonstrating:\n- User registration with validation\n- JWT authentication\n- Error handling"
